OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FLawyers from across the UK have joined
OL,7,Fa march to parliament to oppose the
OL,8,Fgovernment's plans to remove jury
OL,9,Ftrials for some offences, ahead of a
OL,10,Fkey vote today.
OL,12,FThe march's organisers - the London
OL,13,FCriminal Courts Solicitors'
OL,14,FAssociation - told ITV News that the
OL,15,Freforms remove the "fundamental" right
OL,16,Ffor defendants to be "tried by their
OL,17,Fpeers".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FThey called on the government to
OL,7,Finstead consider other reforms to
OL,8,Fbring down the growing crown-court
OL,9,Fbacklog.
OL,11,F"This country has always been built on
OL,12,Fthe fundamental right where defendants
OL,13,Fare tried by their peers or have the
OL,14,Fchoice to be tried by their peers, and
OL,15,Fthese proposals remove that right,"
OL,16,Fthey told ITV News.
OL,18,F"There are other ways to address the
OL,19,Fbacklog by increasing sitting days, by
OL,20,Fopening more courts to ensure cases
OL,21,Fare heard at a quicker rate".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FThe protest comes as MPs are set to
OL,7,Fvote on the reforms when they come in
OL,8,Ffront of the Commons as part of the
OL,9,FCourts and Tribunal bill this
OL,10,Fafternoon.
OL,12,FThe government's proposals would see
OL,13,Fjury trials scrapped in England and
OL,14,FWales for all cases with anticipated
OL,15,Fsentences of less than three years.
OL,16,FInstead, these cases would be decided
OL,17,Fby a single judge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FUnder the plans, only the most serious
OL,7,Foffences - such as rape, murder and
OL,8,Fmanslaughter - would be heard by a
OL,9,Fjury.
OL,11,FEarlier this week, thousands of
OL,12,Fjudges, barristers, and lawyers wrote
OL,13,Fto the prime minister, asking him to
OL,14,F"rethink" his proposals to expand
OL,15,Fjudge-only trials for all cases with
OL,16,Fanticipated sentences of less than
OL,17,Fthree years, arguing they were "based
OL,18,Fon little evidence".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FThe letter, signed by leading legal
OL,7,Ffigures including a former director of
OL,8,Fpublic prosecutions, accused the
OL,9,Fgovernment reforms of being risky, and
OL,10,F"eroding" the "constitutional
OL,11,Fprinciple" of the right to a jury
OL,12,Ftrial for "negligible gain".
OL,14,FHowever, leading victims' groups have
OL,15,Fwelcomed the changes, with the Victims
OL,16,FCommissioner for England and Wales,
OL,17,FClaire Laxman, urging MPs to keep
OL,18,Fvictims at the heart when they vote on
OL,19,Fthe proposals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,F"I have asked countless victims stuck
OL,7,Fin a court system a simple question:
OL,8,Ffaced with waiting years for a jury
OL,9,Ftrial, would they prefer to wait for a
OL,10,Fjury or accept a judge if it meant
OL,11,Fswift justice," she wrote.
OL,13,F"Those enduring the longest waits have
OL,14,Fbeen clear - they would sacrifice the
OL,15,Fwait for a jury if it meant timely
OL,16,Fjustice."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,FJustice Secretary David Lammy has
OL,7,Fdefended his reforms, arguing they
OL,8,Fwill speed up the criminal justice
OL,9,Fprocess and therefore help to tackle
OL,10,Fthe record-high backlog of crown court
OL,11,Fcases, which has more than doubled in
OL,12,Fthe past six years.
OL,14,FWriting in The Telegraph, Lammy said
OL,15,Fthe current system means "offenders
OL,16,Fare left free to roam our streets".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773180726
OL,3,CLawyers march on parliament in protest
OL,4,Cof jury trials plan
OL,6,F"Across Britain today, too many
OL,7,Fvictims endure the same ordeal. For
OL,8,Fthem, justice delayed becomes justice
OL,9,Fdenied. When that happens, offenders
OL,10,Fare left free to roam our streets, and
OL,11,Fmore victims are created," he wrote.
OL,13,FAs well as the changes to jury trials,
OL,14,Fthe justice overhaul would also ramp
OL,15,Fup the use of artificial intelligence
OL,16,F(AI) in court, and the introduction of
OL,17,Ffree legal advice for rape victims to
OL,18,Fhelp try to make their experience less
OL,19,Ftraumatic.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
